thread.title: Canadian Pacific Railway Strike Ends

author: Jacquie McNish
title: Canadian Pacific Railway Strike Ends
text:
TORONTO—A strike that temporarily shut down Canadian Pacific Railway Ltd. operations is over, as the company and the union representing conductors and locomotive engineers on Wednesday reached a tentative four-year deal.
Details of the agreement weren’t immediately available. Teamsters Canada, which represents over 3,000 workers, said operations would resume at 6 a.m. local time across the country. Teamsters members walked off the job at 10 p.m. ET on Tuesday after months of talks failed to produce a deal.
